the berber latin alphabet was also used by most european and berber linguists during the 19th and 20th centuries . 
the name `` tamaziɣt '' is currently being used increasingly by educated berbers to refer to the written berber language ,  and even to berber as a whole ,  including tuareg . 
some other berber writers ,  especially in morocco ,  prefer to refer to berber with `` amazigh '' when writing about it in french or english . 
there are now three writing systems in use for berber languages: tifinagh ,  the arabic script ,  and the berber latin alphabet . 
a modernised form of the tifinagh alphabet ,  called neo-tifinagh ,  was adopted in morocco in 2003 for writing berber ,  but many moroccan berber publications still use the berber latin alphabet . 
berber is a branch of the afroasiatic language family . 
