the branch davidians  -lrb-  also known as the branch  -rrb-  are a religious group that originated in 1955 from a schism among the shepherd's rod/davidians . 
branch davidians are most associated with the waco siege of 1993, which involved david koresh . 
like the branch davidians under koresh ,  this incarnation is waiting for the end of times . 
in the late 1980s ,  koresh and his followers abandoned many branch davidian teachings . 
the seventh-day adventist church issued warnings about the branch davidian views to its members on a regular basis . 
it is claimed that howell was never authorized to use the name `` branch davidians '' for his breakaway sect ,  and that the church of that name continues to represent that part of the branch church which did not follow him . 
branch davidians are considered a splinter group from that dissenting group  -lrb-  the davidians/shephard's rod  -rrb-  and came out from a schism among the davidians/shepherd's rod initiated by benjamin roden . 
one modern incarnation of the branch davidians exists under the leadership of charles pace ,  a follower of ben and lois roden ,  who was a member of the branch davidians since the mid-1970s . 
gate house is one of the four upper houses of the burwash hall residence . 
each upper house consists of three floors . 
gate house ,  with the rest of upper burwash ,  opened in 1913 and has held students every year since then except 1995, when it was renovated . 
gate house has three floors which house 28 students ,  as well as a don and the victoria college residence life co-ordinator . 
the only exception is the view from gate house's tower that looks down st .  mary's street . 
the gate house emblem is the phoenix ,  visible in the bottom-right corner of the victoria college insignia . 
benzodiazepines can be useful for short-term treatment of insomnia . 
older adults should not use benzodiazepines to treat insomnia unless other treatments have failed . 
chlordiazepoxide is the most commonly used benzodiazepine for alcohol detoxification ,  but diazepam may be used as an alternative . 
because of their effectiveness ,  tolerability ,  and rapid onset of anxiolytic action ,  benzodiazepines are frequently used for the treatment of anxiety associated with panic disorder . 
benzodiazepines are usually administered orally; however ,  very occasionally lorazepam or diazepam may be given intravenously for the treatment of panic attacks . 
benzodiazepines are sometimes used in the treatment of acute anxiety ,  as they bring about rapid and marked or moderate relief of symptoms in most individuals; however ,  they are not recommended beyond 2–4 weeks of use due to risks of tolerance and dependence and a lack of long-term effectiveness . 
the list of benzodiazepines approved for the treatment of insomnia is fairly similar among most countries ,  but which benzodiazepines are officially designated as first-line hypnotics prescribed for the treatment of insomnia varies between countries . 
however ,  in some cases ,  a prolonged treatment with benzodiazepines as the add-on to an antidepressant may be justified . 
bmi is used differently for children . 
bmi is proportional to the mass and inversely proportional to the square of the height . 
children with a bmi between the 85th and 95th percentile are considered to be overweight . 
the body mass index  -lrb-  bmi  -rrb-  or quetelet index is a value derived from the mass  -lrb-  weight  -rrb-  and height of an individual . 
the bmi is universally expressed in kg/m ,  resulting from mass in kilograms and height in metres . 
these ranges of bmi values are valid only as statistical categories . 
grotefend had deciphered ten of the 37 symbols of old persian by 1802, after realizing that unlike the semitic cuneiform scripts ,  old persian text is alphabetic and each word is separated by a vertical slanted symbol . 
with the persian text ,  and with about a third of the syllabary made available to him by the work of georg friedrich grotefend ,  rawlinson set to work on deciphering the text . 
after the fall of the persian empire's achaemenid dynasty and its successors ,  and the lapse of old persian cuneiform writing into disuse ,  the nature of the inscription was forgotten ,  and fanciful explanations became the norm . 
the old persian text was copied and deciphered before recovery and copying of the elamite and babylonian inscriptions had even been attempted ,  which proved to be a good deciphering strategy ,  since old persian script was easier to study due to its alphabetic nature and because the language it represents had naturally evolved via middle persian to the living modern persian language dialects ,  and was also related to the avestan language ,  used in the zoroastrian book the `` avesta '' . 
a legend began around mount behistun  -lrb-  bisotun  -rrb-  ,  as written about by the persian poet and writer ferdowsi in his `` shahnameh ''  -lrb-  `` book of kings ''  -rrb-   ,  about a man named farhad ,  who was a lover of king khosrow's wife ,  shirin . 
the translation of the old persian sections of the behistun inscription paved the way to the subsequent ability to decipher the elamite and babylonian parts of the text ,  which greatly promoted the development of modern assyriology . 
the behistun inscription  -lrb-  also bisotun ,  bistun or bisutun;  ,  old persian: bagastana ,  meaning `` the place of god ''  -rrb-  is a multilingual inscription and large rock relief on a cliff at mount behistun in the kermanshah province of iran ,  near the city of kermanshah in western iran ,  established by darius the great  -lrb-  550–486 bc  -rrb-  . 
